The bodies of the boys, aged seven and 10, were discovered by a passerby on Thursday night. JOHANNESBURG - Police in Limpopo says they will conduct autopsies on bodies of two young boys discovered in the veld.Petrus Shoka and Samuel Ngobeni were reported missing last week Wednesday.The bodies of the boys aged seven and 10 were discovered by a passerby on Thursday night near Ga-Chuene in Thokgoaneng.Three sangomas and a woman have been arrested in connection with their murders.Police spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe says: The body parts are still intact, but most of the things will be confirmed by a post-mortem. As of now we re arrested four people - that is three sangomas and one lady. We re still investigated and more arrests are expected. (Edited Zamangwane Shange)